  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mobilising In-Country Resources for Actions Against Poverty</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Primarily, the main idea is to gradually but steadily boost access to locally generated funds for the projects that would not normally receive donor funding and which CCFN is committed to implement. Overtime, the change will be seen in a gradual shift from over dependence on foreign aid for in-country projects to a supplementary role &#x2013; Promoting Shifting the Power Concept. This obviously will strengthen the culture of awareness in mobilizing and generating local funds. Increasing the access to unrestricted funds is key to CCFN&#x2019;s sustainability, but fundamentally; launching into in-country resource mobilisation through the right process and taking into consideration all the constraints involved. 
Therefore the overarching goal of this project is to build and sustain a realistic culture within the Catholic Faithful in Nigeria which paves the way for access to a world of funds for the noble humanitarian and developmental works that CCFN are privileged to be a part of. 
CCFN through the local priest in-charge of parishes. Based on the subsidiarity policy within the Church, CCFN needs the approval of any priest to talk fund-raise within the parish and the Bishop to fund-raise within any diocese. CCFN will engage with about 50 parishes in 2 Archdioceses.</narrative>
  </description>
